OL,3,CPassenger denied boarding her flight
OL,4,Cbecause of her epilepsy
OL,6,FWhen approaching the boarding gate, a
OL,7,Frepresentative of the aviation
OL,8,Fservices company, Swissport, told the
OL,9,Fstudent nurse that the cabin crew "did
OL,10,Fnot feel comfortable" having a
OL,11,Fpassenger with epilepsy on the flight.
OL,13,FMs Bownes was told that if she were to
OL,14,Fhave a seizure, the crew were not
OL,15,Fconfident in their ability to
OL,16,Fadminister her medication, even though
OL,17,Fshe had already declared she could
OL,18,Fself-administer in the initial phone
OL,19,Fcall with Loganair.
